<Window x:Class="StockUI.PopUp.HelpScreen"
        xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml/presentation"
        xmlns:x="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml"
        xmlns:d="http://schemas.microsoft.com/expression/blend/2008"
        xmlns:mc="http://schemas.openxmlformats.org/markup-compatibility/2006"
        xmlns:local="clr-namespace:StockUI.PopUp"
        mc:Ignorable="d"
        Title="HelpScreen" Height="450" Width="500">
    <Grid Height ="350" Width="450" >
        <Grid.ColumnDefinitions>
            <ColumnDefinition Width="56*"/>
            <ColumnDefinition Width="169*"/>
        </Grid.ColumnDefinitions>
        <ScrollViewer Grid.ColumnSpan="2">
            <TextBlock Width="Auto"  HorizontalAlignment="Left" Margin="10,10,0,0" TextWrapping="Wrap" VerticalAlignment="Top" ><Run Text="Here is an overview of the tool and their functionality!"/><LineBreak/><Run/><LineBreak/><Run Text="1. Fundamentals"/><LineBreak/><Run Text="This tool handles the gathering and processing of past fundamental data. "/><LineBreak/><Run Text="&#x9;Select Month: The months will be generated from the file names in the earnings folder. A month must be selected before all operations except for date gathering."/><LineBreak/><Run Text="&#x9;Extract From HTML: The first operation, where data is extracted from the IBD earnings files and displayed. From here you will either gather or add fundamentals"/><LineBreak/><Run Text="&#x9;Add Fundamentals: This operation is only possible when data has previously been gathered. Otherwise it will display a blank window.  Data is displayed from saved CSV files for easy viewing."/><LineBreak/><Run Text="&#x9;Gather Fundamentals: This operation will gather fundamentals for all symbols in the currently selected month, and save them in the Fundamentals folder under the current month. Progress is displayed in the title bar. Date gathering MUST be done BEFORE this operation. If run beforehand simply skip this step. "/><LineBreak/><Run Text="&#x9;Get Dates: This is the accompanying date gatherer. Simply click it and it will gather the dates for ALL months. This operation is only needed the before the first gathering."/><LineBreak/><Run Text="&#x9;Get Comparisons: This operation builds the list of all possible stock comparisons for the current month, and saves it locally in the Results folder under the currently selected minimum gain subfolder. "/><LineBreak/><Run Text="&#x9;Show Errors: This is used to display any API errors during fundamental gathering. When a symbol does not have a fundamental calculated it will display a text box alerting you. This is for debugging purposes, and is not necessary for normal operations. "/><LineBreak/><Run/><LineBreak/><Run Text="2. Comparisons"/><LineBreak/><Run Text="This tool displays all months of comparisons along with some generated statistics for review and analysis"/><LineBreak/><Run Text="&#x9;Get All Comparisons: This operation will gather all comparison files from the Results folder and display them. A combined file with the added statistics is saves in a Combined subfolder in current minimum gains Results folder."/><LineBreak/><Run Text="&#x9;Exclude Partial Results: This will exclude tests not present in all data's months from the results displayed. Excluded tests are still saved locally for later display if desired. Success rates and averages are calculated assuming all months are present, so missing months take a flat hit to their results. "/><LineBreak/><Run/><LineBreak/><Run Text="3. Individual Tests"/><LineBreak/><Run Text="&#x9;Select Month: The months will be generated from the file names in the earnings folder. A month must be selected before all operations except for date gathering."/><LineBreak/><Run Text="&#x9;Get HTML: The first operation, where data is extracted from the IBD earnings files and displayed. From here you will gather fundamentals"/><LineBreak/><Run Text="&#x9;Get Dates: This is the accompanying date gatherer. Simply click it and it will gather the dates for ALL months. This operation is only needed the before the first gathering or prediction. If run beforehand simply skip this step. "/><LineBreak/><Run Text="&#x9;Predict: This will gather all fundamentals for the coming month's data. If data is already gathered it will display fundamental data with the provided filters. Gain cannot be generated as expected, and all results are saved locally in the FutureFundamentals folder. "/><LineBreak/><Run Text="&#x9;Show Errors: This is used to display any API errors during fundamental gathering. When a symbol does not have a fundamental calculated it will display a text box alerting you. This is for debugging purposes, and is not necessary for normal operations. "/><LineBreak/><Run Text="&#x9;Fundamentals Inputs: Will display fundamentals with provided minimum requirements. This allows you to test combinations from Comparisons. All fundamentals are saved regardless of filter. "/><LineBreak/><Run/><LineBreak/><Run Text="4. Settings "/><LineBreak/><Run Text="This allows you to configure the tools. If not set they will use my defaults (Delay 15000 (15 seconds), Gain .98 (Not lose more than 2%), Growth 1.35 (35% growth), and Price 5 (Over $5 per share))"/><LineBreak/><Run Text="&#x9;API Key: This is gotten at alphavantage.com. A new API key is needed for the first time setup. For now my API key is included."/><LineBreak/><Run Text="&#x9;Minimum Delay: Corresponds to tier of API key. You can pay for a lower delay. Currently a basic free key is 15 seconds. Seconds * 1000 = Minimum Delay."/><LineBreak/><Run Text="&#x9;Minimum Gain: Sets the minimum gain per share to be listed as a success. "/><LineBreak/><Run Text="&#x9;Minimum Growth: Sets the minimum growth to be included as a symbol from the HTML files."/><LineBreak/><Run Text="&#x9;Minimum Price: Sets the minimum price to be included as a symbol from the HTML files. "/><LineBreak/><Run/></TextBlock>
        </ScrollViewer>
    </Grid >
</Window>
